    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S), a masterclass in front-midship engineering. This specimen features the iconic 13B-REW rotary engine, maintaining exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The sequential twin-turbocharging system operates with factory precision, utilizing the complex vacuum-actuated pre-spool logic for seamless power delivery. The chassis retains its original 50:50 weight distribution, supported by a pristine double-wishbone suspension setup and a Torsen limited-slip differential for surgical handling. Every component, from the oil metering pump to the cooling system's thermal management, remains in peak operational status. A true time-capsule example for the discerning collector who demands mechanical perfection and structural rigidity.",
      "price": 48500.0,
